<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="specifying-viewers-for-published-documents" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Specifying Viewers for Published Documents</title>
  <taskbody id="body">
    <context>
      <p>In Serna, you can  <xref href="publishing.xml" scope="local">publish</xref> a file to some format (for information about publishing specifications, see <xref href="../developers_guide/publishing.xml"/>). Then it is possible to call an external file viewer from Serna to view published files. </p>
      <p>To specify external applications for viewing published files, do the following: </p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>, choose <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
            </menucascade>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <keyword>Applications tab</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <fig>
            <title>Applications tab.</title>
            <image href="preferences-dialog-applications-tab.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To add a file viewer, do the following:</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Add</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>In the <keyword>File Handler Dialog</keyword>, specify the file extension and corresponding application. Click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info>
              <fig>
                <title>File Handler Dialog.</title>
                <image href="file-handler-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
              </fig>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To edit a file viewer settings, do the following:</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Select the file viewer and click the <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>In the <keyword>File Handler Dialog</keyword>, modify the file extension and/or application. Click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</cmd>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To delete a file viewer, select it and click the <uicontrol>Delete</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol> button to apply the settings.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the dialog.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
